{
  "text": "miRNA-based therapeutics represent a promising approach for cancer therapy [CITATION_1] . Recent years, numerous preclinical studies have been conducted with miRNA therapeutics. The miRNAs therapeutics has some changlleges for miRNA delivery vehicles, tissue-specific targeting, off-target effects and potential toxicities [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . MRX34 is a liposome-formulated double-stranded mimic of tumor suppressor miR-34, which is lost or expressed at reduced levels in many solid and hematologic malignancies. A multicenter phase I clinical trial of MRX34 is being conducted in patients with unresectable solid tumors. MRX34 treatment showed evidence of antitumor activity in a subset of patients with refractory advanced solid tumors. However, owing to immune-related adverse events involving patient deaths, the trial was terminated [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] .",
